<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1301,1807]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1341,1367]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male FW length range 39.8–41.3 mm (based on specimens in Appendix 
<number box="[1251,1265,1341,1367]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1.0">1</number>
). Wings with orange-brown background. FW orange postmedial band markedly reduced, broken into a series of independent spots that do not reach the anterior FW margin. HW with a thin orange marginal band. Males have a thin hairpencil inside HW discal cell, contrasting other species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[912,979,1461,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Opoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aorsa">
<emphasis box="[912,979,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">aorsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
